pointer is dervived data type in c

pointer contain memory addresses as their value

can be used to acces and manipulate data stored in the memory 

pointer value : the address of a variable obtained through addres operator can be store in another variable called pointer variable "&"

the "&" operator can be used with a simple variable or an array element


accessing a variable throug its pointer done by using unary operator "*"(*p means value at addres p)

